<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 RB005 Week 1 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Design Your Game — One Mechanic, One Map · <strong>Course:</strong> Dream Game Studio · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This is YOUR game now. Before you build anything, you need a plan: what does the player <strong>do</strong>, and how do they <strong>win</strong>? Great games start small — <strong>one mechanic, one map</strong>.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Think 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each question. Write what you think before class.</p>
<p><strong>A core loop is what the player does again and again. In tag, the loop is: run → chase → tag → run again. What is the loop in an obby (jumping game)?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>A win condition tells the player when they are done. Imagine a game with no win condition — it just never ends. Why might players quit a game that never says "You win!"?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>You have 4 weeks. Game A has one mechanic and one map. Game B has pets, 100 levels, and an open world. Which one will actually be FINISHED in 4 weeks? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Fix the Design 🐛</h2>
<p>A student wrote this design. It sounds amazing — and it is way too big to ever finish.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>My game:</strong> An open world with 100 levels, a pet system, a shop, multiplayer battles, and a city you can build yourself.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Your job: cut it down to <strong>one mechanic, one map</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Which ONE part would you keep for version 1? Why that one?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Rewrite the design as one sentence with one mechanic and one map.</strong> (Shape: "Players ___ to ___ on one ___ map.")</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>The cut features are not deleted forever — they go on a "later list." Why is a later list better than trying to build everything now?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now write YOUR design doc — on paper or in a doc. It needs four things: your game in <strong>one sentence</strong>, the <strong>loop</strong> (what the player does every 30 seconds), the <strong>win condition</strong>, and <strong>3 dream features</strong> with a circle around the ONE you will build for version 1.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your design doc, then explain it here. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My game in one sentence is …</p>
<p>Every 30 seconds, the player …</p>
<p>You win when …</p>
<p>My three dream features are …</p>
<p>For version 1, I circled … because …</p>
<p>If version 1 goes well, next I would add …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) and <strong>pitch your game in 1 minute</strong>, like you are selling it to a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>mechanic</strong>, <strong>loop</strong>, <strong>win condition</strong>, <strong>version 1</strong>, <strong>player</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Say your game's name and your one-sentence idea.</li>
<li>Explain the loop: what the player does every 30 seconds.</li>
<li>Say the win condition.</li>
<li>Say which ONE feature you picked for version 1 — and why you cut the rest.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
